Luis Suarez is being protected by armed soldiers at the Uruguay team hotel after he controversially bit Giorgio Chiellini on Tuesday.

Security around the striker has been stepped up, with military police surrounding the Serhs Hotel in Natal where the Uruguay team are staying.

Truckloads of soldiers sat outside the hotel, while more armed guards patrolled the area as pressure grows on FIFA to ban the controversial forward.

