Uruguay qualified from Group D thanks to a Diego Godin goal, but the result was overshadowed by Suarez's bite on Chiellini.

FIFA has launched disciplinary proceedings against the Liverpool striker, and given Uruguay until 9pm on Wednesday to respond.

If Suarez is found guilty he could be banned for up to two years, although the longest ban in World Cup history is eight games.

